# Requirements Sync

When changing user-facing behavior, defaults, data integrations, validation, routing, map behavior,
recommendation logic, deployment behavior, or acceptance criteria, check `SOFTWARE_REQUIREMENTS.md`.

If the change affects requirements or prototype status, update the document in the same branch:

- Update the relevant requirement or prototype-status section.
- Update acceptance criteria when behavior becomes implemented or changes scope.
- Add a short running-progress entry for notable product changes.
- Increment the document history version for meaningful requirements updates.

Do not leave shipped behavior undocumented just because the code change is small.
